{"title":"just want to try again","note":"ok","poem":"An autumn morning\non Jay Street\nfour men with green eyes\nwhispering about someone who never caught the train\n\nA summer midnight\noutside a laundromat in Flushing\nthree boys with green hair\nsinging about someone who never cried\n\nA winter afternoon\non the downtown F train\ntwo boys with pink hair\ngossiping about someone who never lit the candle\n\nA spring midnight\non a rooftop in Bushwick\nfour women with pink hair\nlistening to stories about someone who never learned the song","createdAt":{"$$date":1772793329136},"_id":"Iu3KZOVmd0oeasX3"}
{"title":"untitled","note":"cute!","poem":"A summer midnight\nbetween two subway stops\nthree boys with brown eyes\nwaiting for someone who never found the way home\n\nA winter midday\nin the back seat of a yellow cab\nfour people with brown hair\npainting images about someone who never made a wish\n\nA spring morning\nat a table near the door\ntwo boys with green hair\ndreaming aloud about someone who never told a lie\n\nAn autumn morning\non a rooftop in Bushwick\nfour women with pink hair\nreflecting about someone who never woke up","createdAt":{"$$date":1772793211801},"_id":"Q4GXjEBWXNrlBM4W"}
{"title":"test","note":"please work","poem":"An autumn midnight\ncrossing the Williamsburg Bridge\ntwo people wearing white sneakers\nrecording sounds about someone who never fed the cats\n\nA summer evening\non a rooftop in Bushwick\nthree women with green hair\nlecturing about someone who never chased the pigeons\n\nA spring midnight\nin the back seat of a yellow cab\nfour women carrying luggage\nfighting about someone who never asked why\n\nA winter afternoon\nin a basement in Chinatown\nfour girls all suited up\nsinging about someone who never lost the map","createdAt":{"$$date":1772791999006},"_id":"nAdnpnVxPPVp08VF"}
